org.eclipse.keyple.core.plugin

Class AbstractObservablePlugin

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.keyple.core.plugin.AbstractPlugin
      • org.eclipse.keyple.core.plugin.AbstractObservablePlugin
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ObservablePluginNotifier, ObservablePlugin, Plugin
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractThreadedObservablePlugin

    public abstract class AbstractObservablePlugin
extends AbstractPlugin
implements ObservablePluginNotifier
    Provides the means to manage the observation of a plugin.

    It allows:

    • the management of the observers (add/remove/count) (see the ObservablePlugin.PluginObserver interface)
    • the notification of PluginEvent to all the observers
    Since:
    0.9

    • Method Detail

      • addObserver

        public void addObserver(ObservablePlugin.PluginObserver observer)
        Register a new plugin observer to be notified when a plugin event occurs.

        The provided observer will receive all the events produced by this plugin (reader connection, disconnection).

        It is possible to add as many observers as necessary. They will be notified of events sequentially in the order in which they are added.

        Specified by:
        addObserver in interface ObservablePlugin
        Parameters:
        observer - An observer object implementing the required interface (should be not null).
        Since:
        0.9

      • removeObserver

        public void removeObserver(ObservablePlugin.PluginObserver observer)
        Unregister a plugin observer.

        The observer will no longer receive any of the events produced by this plugin.

        Specified by:
        removeObserver in interface ObservablePlugin
        Parameters:
        observer - The observer object to be unregistered (should be not null).
